msgid "So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā."
msgstr "There he sees a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes."

msgctxt "an5.76:10.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ "
"anuddhaṃseti."
msgstr "Lust infects his mind,"

msgctxt "an5.76:10.5"
msgid "So rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena pariḍayhateva kāyena pariḍayhati cetasā."
msgstr "and his body and mind burn with it."

msgctxt "an5.76:10.6"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "He thinks:"

msgctxt "an5.76:10.7"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ āroceyyaṃ—"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I go to the monastery and tell the monks:"

msgctxt "an5.76:10.8"
msgid ""
"rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi, āvuso, rāgapareto, na sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, I am overcome with lust, mired in lust. I am unable to keep up "
"the spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.76:10.9"
msgid "sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to "
"a lesser life.”’"

msgctxt "an5.76:10.10"
msgid "So ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ āroceti:"
msgstr "He goes to the monastery and tells the monks:"

msgctxt "an5.76:10.11"
msgid ""
"‘rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi, āvuso, rāgapareto, na sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ "
"sandhāretuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, I am overcome with lust, mired in lust. I am unable to keep up "
"the spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.76:10.12"
msgid "sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to "
"a lesser life.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.97"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:11.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sabrahmacārī ovadanti anusāsanti:"
msgstr "His spiritual companions advise and instruct him:"

#. VAR: bahupāyāsā → bahūpāyāsā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.76:11.2"
msgid ""
"‘appassādā, āvuso, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification "
"and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks."

msgctxt "an5.76:11.3"
msgid ""
"Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr "With the similes of a skeleton …"

msgctxt "an5.76:11.4"
msgid ""
"Maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr "a piece of flesh …"

msgctxt "an5.76:11.5"
msgid ""
"Tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo."
msgstr "a grass torch …"

msgctxt "an5.76:11.6"
msgid ""
"Aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr "a pit of glowing coals …"

msgctxt "an5.76:11.7"
msgid ""
"Supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr "a dream …"

msgctxt "an5.76:11.8"
msgid ""
"Yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr "borrowed goods …"

msgctxt "an5.76:11.9"
msgid ""
"Rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr "fruit on a tree …"

msgctxt "an5.76:11.10"
msgid ""
"Asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo."
msgstr "a butcher’s knife and chopping block …"

msgctxt "an5.76:11.11"
msgid ""
"Sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr "a staking sword …"

msgctxt "an5.76:11.12"
msgid ""
"Sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"a snake’s head, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little "
"gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more "
"full of drawbacks."

msgctxt "an5.76:11.13"
msgid "Abhiramatāyasmā brahmacariye;"
msgstr "Be happy with the spiritual life."

# I don’t know why BB has “think” here, the text as always has avikatva (declare). Also note the use of “venerable”, as contrasted with “avuso” earlier.
msgctxt "an5.76:11.14"
msgid "māyasmā sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattī’ti."
msgstr ""
"Venerable, please don’t declare your inability to continue training, reject "
"it and return to a lesser life.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:12.1"
msgid "So sabrahmacārīhi evaṃ ovadiyamāno evaṃ anusāsiyamāno evamāha:"
msgstr "When thus advised and instructed by his spiritual companions, he says:"

msgctxt "an5.76:12.2"
msgid ""
"‘kiñcāpi, āvuso, appassādā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, "
"ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo;"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, even though the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little "
"gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more "
"full of drawbacks,"

msgctxt "an5.76:12.3"
msgid ""
"atha kho nevāhaṃ sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ, sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā "
"sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I am unable to keep up the spiritual life. I declare my inability to "
"continue training. I reject it and will return to a lesser life.’"

msgctxt "an5.76:12.4"
msgid "So sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati."
msgstr ""
"Declaring his inability to continue training, he rejects it and returns to a "
"lesser life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.98"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:13.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ "
"sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, "
"tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare upalikkhanti, tamenaṃ apanenti; apanetvā "
"ñātakānaṃ nenti, tamenaṃ ñātakā upaṭṭhahanti paricaranti. So ñātakehi "
"upaṭṭhahiyamāno paricariyamāno teneva ābādhena kālaṃ karoti; tathūpamāhaṃ, "
"bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"I say that this person is like the warrior who dies of his injuries while in "
"the care of his relatives. Some people are like that."

msgctxt "an5.76:13.2"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu."
msgstr "This is the third person similar to a warrior found among the monks."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:14.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya "
"viharati."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant lives supported by a town or village."

msgctxt "an5.76:14.2"
msgid ""
"So pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya tameva gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā "
"piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena "
"anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā asaṃvutehi indriyehi."
msgstr ""
"He robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters a village "
"or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without "
"establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties."

msgctxt "an5.76:14.3"
msgid "So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā."
msgstr "There he sees a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes."

msgctxt "an5.76:14.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ "
"anuddhaṃseti."
msgstr "Lust infects his mind,"

msgctxt "an5.76:14.5"
msgid "So rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena pariḍayhateva kāyena pariḍayhati cetasā."
msgstr "and his body and mind burn with it."

msgctxt "an5.76:14.6"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "He thinks:"

msgctxt "an5.76:14.7"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ āroceyyaṃ—"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I go to the monastery and tell the monks:"

msgctxt "an5.76:14.8"
msgid ""
"rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi, āvuso, rāgapareto, na sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, I am overcome with lust, mired in lust. I am unable to keep up "
"the spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.76:14.9"
msgid "sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to "
"a lesser life.”’"

msgctxt "an5.76:14.10"
msgid "So ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ āroceti:"
msgstr "He goes to the monastery and tells the monks:"

msgctxt "an5.76:14.11"
msgid ""
"‘rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi, āvuso, rāgapareto, na sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ "
"sandhāretuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, I am overcome with lust, mired in lust. I am unable to keep up "
"the spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.76:14.12"
msgid "sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to "
"a lesser life.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.99"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:15.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sabrahmacārī ovadanti anusāsanti:"
msgstr "His spiritual companions advise and instruct him:"

msgctxt "an5.76:15.2"
msgid ""
"‘appassādā, āvuso, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification "
"and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks."

msgctxt "an5.76:15.3"
msgid ""
"Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr "With the simile of a skeleton …"

msgctxt "an5.76:15.4"
msgid ""
"Maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … pe … tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … "
"aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … "
"yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … "
"asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … "
"sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"a piece of flesh … a grass torch … a pit of glowing coals … a dream … "
"borrowed goods … fruit on a tree … a butcher’s knife and chopping block … a "
"staking sword … a snake’s head, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give "
"little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the "
"more full of drawbacks."

msgctxt "an5.76:15.5"
msgid "Abhiramatāyasmā brahmacariye;"
msgstr "Be happy with the spiritual life."

msgctxt "an5.76:15.6"
msgid "māyasmā sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattī’ti."
msgstr ""
"Venerable, please don’t declare your inability to continue training, reject "
"it and return to a lesser life.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:16.1"
msgid "So sabrahmacārīhi evaṃ ovadiyamāno evaṃ anusāsiyamāno evamāha:"
msgstr "When thus advised and instructed by his spiritual companions, he says:"

msgctxt "an5.76:16.2"
msgid "‘ussahissāmi, āvuso, vāyamissāmi, āvuso, abhiramissāmi, āvuso."
msgstr "‘I’ll try, reverends, I’ll struggle, I’ll be happy."

msgctxt "an5.76:16.3"
msgid ""
"Na dānāhaṃ, āvuso, sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya "
"hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I won’t now declare my inability to continue training, reject it and return "
"to a lesser life.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:17.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ "
"sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, "
"tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare upalikkhanti, tamenaṃ apanenti; apanetvā "
"ñātakānaṃ nenti, tamenaṃ ñātakā upaṭṭhahanti paricaranti. So ñātakehi "
"upaṭṭhahiyamāno paricariyamāno vuṭṭhāti tamhā ābādhā; tathūpamāhaṃ, "
"bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"I say that this person is like the warrior who recovers from his injuries "
"while in the care of his relatives."

msgctxt "an5.76:17.2"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti."
msgstr "Some people are like that."

msgctxt "an5.76:17.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu."
msgstr "This is the fourth person similar to a warrior found among the monks."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.100"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:18.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya "
"viharati."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant lives supported by a town or village."

msgctxt "an5.76:18.2"
msgid ""
"So pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya tameva gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā "
"piṇḍāya pavisati rakkhiteneva kāyena rakkhitāya vācāya rakkhitena cittena "
"upaṭṭhitāya satiyā saṃvutehi indriyehi."
msgstr ""
"He robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters a village "
"or town, guarding body, speech, and mind, establishing mindfulness, and "
"restraining the sense faculties."

msgctxt "an5.76:18.3"
msgid "So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"Seeing a sight with his eyes, he doesn’t get caught up in the features and "
"details."

msgctxt "an5.76:18.4"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati "
"cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, he practices "
"restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving restraint over it."

msgctxt "an5.76:18.5"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … "
msgstr "Hearing a sound with his ears … "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.6"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … "
msgstr "Smelling an odor with his nose … "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.7"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … "
msgstr "Tasting a flavor with his tongue … "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.8"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … "
msgstr "Feeling a touch with his body … "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.9"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"Knowing a thought with his mind, he doesn’t get caught up in the features "
"and details."

msgctxt "an5.76:18.10"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati "
"manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, he practices "
"restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving restraint over it."

msgctxt "an5.76:18.11"
msgid "So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto "
msgstr "Then after the meal, on his return from alms-round, "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.12"
msgid ""
"vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ "
"susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"he frequents a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a "
"ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of "
"straw."

msgctxt "an5.76:18.13"
msgid ""
"So araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ "
"ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"Gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, he sits "
"down cross-legged, with his body straight, and establishes mindfulness right "
"there."

msgctxt "an5.76:18.14"
msgid ""
"So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya … pe … so ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso "
"upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
msgstr ""
"He gives up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken "
"wisdom. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.15"
msgid "vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful "
"qualities, he enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption "
"… third absorption … fourth absorption."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:19.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When his mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"flawless, rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—"
"he extends it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an5.76:19.2"
msgid ""
"So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"He truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’"
" … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads "
"to the cessation of suffering’. He truly understands: ‘These are defilements’"
" … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of "
"defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of "
"defilements’. Knowing and seeing like this, his mind is freed from the "
"defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. When freed, "
"he knows ‘it is freed’. He understands: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual "
"journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no "
"return to any state of existence.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an5.76:20.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ "
"sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so taṃ saṅgāmaṃ abhivijinitvā "
"vijitasaṅgāmo tameva saṅgāmasīsaṃ ajjhāvasati; tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ "
"puggalaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"I say that this person is like the warrior who dons his sword and shield, "
"fastens his bow and arrows, and plunges into the thick of battle. He wins "
"victory in battle, establishing himself as foremost in battle."

msgctxt "an5.76:20.2"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti."
msgstr "Some people are like that."

msgctxt "an5.76:20.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu."
msgstr "This is the fifth person similar to a warrior found among the monks."

msgctxt "an5.76:20.4"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca yodhājīvūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā "
"bhikkhūsū”ti."
msgstr "These five people similar to warriors are found among the monks.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.76:20.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
